Available Tools: get_historical_readings | get_average_reading | get_min_max | export_sensor_data
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "sensor_id": "string", "from": "string", "to": "string", "interval": "string" }
Response Schema: { "sensor_id": "string", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "string", "value": number }], "avg": number, "min": number, "max": number }
---
Question: Retrieve the minimum and maximum temperature readings for sensor TEMP-001 in the warehouse between yesterday morning and tonight, using an hourly interval.
Call: { "func_call": "get_min_max", "sensor_id": "TEMP-001", "from": "2023-10-25T08:00:00Z", "to": "2023-10-26T20:00:00Z", "interval": "1h" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "TEMP-001", "readings": [], "avg": 22.4, "min": 18.2, "max": 26.7 }

Question: Export all humidity data from sensor HUM-404 located in the greenhouse for the last week as a CSV file for the agricultural team.
Call: { "func_call": "export_sensor_data", "sensor_id": "HUM-404", "from": "2023-10-19T00:00:00Z", "to": "2023-10-26T23:59:59Z", "interval": "15m" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "HUM-404", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "2023-10-26T12:00:00Z", "value": 65.2 }, { "timestamp": "2023-10-26T12:15:00Z", "value": 66.1 }], "avg": 64.8, "min": 45.0, "max": 82.3 }

Question: Check sensor PRESS-99 in the boiler room for any pressure anomalies by getting the min and max values over the last 24 hours with 10-minute intervals.
Call: { "func_call": "get_min_max", "sensor_id": "PRESS-99", "from": "2023-10-25T14:30:00Z", "to": "2023-10-26T14:30:00Z", "interval": "10m" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "PRESS-99", "readings": [], "avg": 101.3, "min": 98.5, "max": 105.8 }

Question: Generate a CSV export of vibration data for motor sensor VIB-202 from the start of the shift until now to analyze potential equipment failure.
Call: { "func_call": "export_sensor_data", "sensor_id": "VIB-202", "from": "2023-10-26T06:00:00Z", "to": "2023-10-26T14:00:00Z", "interval": "1m" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "VIB-202", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "2023-10-26T13:58:00Z", "value": 4.2 }, { "timestamp": "2023-10-26T13:59:00Z", "value": 4.5 }], "avg": 3.8, "min": 2.1, "max": 6.9 }

Question: What were the lowest and highest CO2 levels recorded by sensor AIR-101 in the conference room during the all-hands meeting yesterday?
Call: { "func_call": "get_min_max", "sensor_id": "AIR-101", "from": "2023-10-25T10:00:00Z", "to": "2023-10-25T12:00:00Z", "interval": "5m" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "AIR-101", "readings": [], "avg": 850.0, "min": 420.0, "max": 1200.0 }

Question: Export the full light intensity log from sensor LUX-303 on the factory floor for the entire month of October to check for lighting consistency.
Call: { "func_call": "export_sensor_data", "sensor_id": "LUX-303", "from": "2023-10-01T00:00:00Z", "to": "2023-10-31T23:59:59Z", "interval": "30m" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "LUX-303", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "2023-10-31T09:00:00Z", "value": 520.0 }, { "timestamp": "2023-10-31T09:30:00Z", "value": 515.0 }], "avg": 480.5, "min": 10.0, "max": 850.0 }

Question: Identify potential freezing events by retrieving the min and max temperatures from sensor FREEZE-05 in the cold storage unit over the last 48 hours.
Call: { "func_call": "get_min_max", "sensor_id": "FREEZE-05", "from": "2023-10-24T14:00:00Z", "to": "2023-10-26T14:00:00Z", "interval": "1h" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "FREEZE-05", "readings": [], "avg": -18.5, "min": -22.1, "max": -15.3 }

Question: Create a downloadable CSV report of water flow rates from sensor FLOW-77 at the treatment plant for the weekend to detect any leaks.
Call: { "func_call": "export_sensor_data", "sensor_id": "FLOW-77", "from": "2023-10-21T00:00:00Z", "to": "2023-10-22T23:59:59Z", "interval": "10m" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "FLOW-77", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "2023-10-21T12:00:00Z", "value": 120.5 }, { "timestamp": "2023-10-21T12:10:00Z", "value": 122.1 }], "avg": 115.2, "min": 90.0, "max": 145.8 }

